24. They believed they were [working] well practiced<lb/>
and deceived themselves, being quite wrong.<lb/>
Because they thought that his works were done <lb/>
without effort, though the extreme powers<lb/>
of Art were achieved with difficulty.<lb/>
 For one sees his pictures repainted<lb/>
and covered with several layers of colors.<lb/>
They required much more effort than one would think.<lb/>
</ab>

<ab><margin>left-middle</margin>Many intend to imitate Titian and become lost.</ab>

</div>

